<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blair Says Britain Prepared to Use Force on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said Wednesday that Britain was prepared to use force on Kosovo
although it still hoped for a peaceful solution to the worsening
crisis in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in British parliament, Blair made it clear that his
country would not hesitate to use force to defuse the current
crisis if diplomatic efforts failed.
</P>
<P>
"We hope over the next few days there will be the right mixture
of political and diplomatic initiatives. We are prepared to use
force if the political and diplomatic efforts fail," Blair said.
</P>
<P>
On whether NATO military action should need U.N. Security
Council agreement, Blair said: "We will of course make sure that
we have a proper legal basis."  
</P>
</TEXT>
