<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong SAR Anniversary Celebrated in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Economic and Trade
Office in Singapore held a grand cocktail reception here Wednesday
to mark the 1st anniversary of the establishment of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception which was attended by more than 1,000
guests including Chinese Ambassador to Singapore Chen Baoliu,
Director of the office Thomas Tso said: "there are still vivid
memories about the historical moment when Hong Kong returned to
the motherland."
</P>
<P>
From then, "Hong Kong entered into a new era eagerly
anticipating the challenges and opportunities," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the situation in Hong Kong, Thomas Tso said: "The guiding
principle of 'one country, two systems' has been put into
practice. The rule of law is well preserved and a level playing
field is zealously maintained. The lifestyle of Hong Kong people
remains intact and the community is open, tolerant and vibrant as
ever."
</P>
<P>
While noting that Hong Kong In the past 12 months had
"encountered many challenges, perhaps a few more than we have
bargained for," he added: "We must not lose sight of the seamless
transition we have experienced."
</P>
<P>
Citing the financial turmoil in Asia and its knock-on effects
on Hong Kong, the director said Hong Kong is undergoing a period
of major economic adjustment and is sure to maintain and further
improve its competitive edge in the years to come.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident that Hong Kong has the strength to ride out
the storm and emerge stronger," Thomas Tso emphasized.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong will continue the efforts to maintain the
stability of the Hong Kong dollar through its pegged rate with the
U.S. dollar, and will, as a major international business and
financial center, carry on its role in facilitating trade and
investment flow in the region.
</P>
<P>
"With the will, ability and determination to press ahead with
our vision and close cooperation with our partners in Asia," he
said, "we in Hong Kong believe that the whole of Asia will soon be
able to be back on our feet."
</P>
<P>
"Looking ahead, difficult times may still be with us for a
while," but "we certainly are looking forward to a brighter future
in the next millennium," he said.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, a video presentation by SAR Chief Executive
Tung Chee Hwa on the occasion was shown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
