<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Record 26-million TV Audience for England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A record-breaking 26 million Britain
audience watched England crash out of the World Cup in a penalty
shoot-out against Argentina, broadcasters said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An average 23.7 million fans tuned in to Tuesday night's match
on Britain's commercial ITV network, the highest since the
channel was established in 1955. The audience share was 80
percent, ITV said.
</P>
<P>
The number of viewers rose to 26 million - the highest number
for a single channel - at the start of the heart-breaking
shoot-out which Argentina won 4-3 to book a place in the
quarter-final of the tournament in France.
</P>
<P>
Only two other shows have ever commanded a higher audience on
British television - the Christmas 1996 edition of the BBC sitcom
Only Fools And Horses with 24.3 million and a November 1979
broadcast To The Manor Born on BBC with 23.9 million when ITV
programes were blacked out by a strike. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
