<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Urges India to Join Nuclear Test Ban Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on
Wednesday urged India to join the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban
Treaty without delay, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a message sent to Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihary
Vajpayee, Yeltsin said such a move on the part of New Delhi would
be welcomed by the international community.
</P>
<P>
"The whole world would welcome the accession of your country to
the Non-Proliferation Treaty," Yeltsin said. "This problem must be
solved."
</P>
<P>
India carried out five nuclear tests in May, drawing world-wide
condemnations. Neighboring Pakistan conducted six nuclear
explosions two weeks later in a nuclear arms race that runs
counter to the world trend of nuclear disarmament.  
</P>
