<HEADLINE> UK to Publish Bill on Convention Banning Landmines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said Wednesday his government would publish a bill next week to
ratify the Ottawa Convention on banning landmines.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the government decision in parliament, Blair said
that he hoped that the British parliament could get the bill
approved by the end of July.
</P>
<P>
Blair stressed that Britain hoped to be among the first 40
countries in the world to ratify the crucial convention on banning
all landmines.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said in a
statement issued Wednesday afternoon: "This legislation will make
sure that we can meet our international obligations in full when
the Ottawa Convention enters into force."
</P>
<P>
"It will also provide a clear legal framework for our armed
forces to carry out their duties," Cook added in the statement.
</P>
