<HEADLINE> Lesotho Opposition Parties Refuse to Accept </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Three major opposition parties in
Lesotho have petitioned the high court to nullify results of the
general elections in May, Southern African Broadcasting Association
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In their legal action, the Basotho Congress Party, the Basotho
National Party and Marematlou Freedom Party alleged that the ruling
Lesotho Congress for Democracy rigged the polls.
</P>
<P>
At least 208 candidates want the ballot papers used in the
polling on May 23 to be examined by electoral officials in
their presence.
</P>
<P>
About 1.3 million eligible voters cast their votes to choose
their legislators for the next five years.
</P>
<P>
The Lesotho Congress for Democracy won 78 of the 80 seats of the
National Assembly. Independent monitors of the elections declared
the vote free and fair.
</P>
<P>
The Kingdom of Lesotho, with a population of about two million
people, last held its elections in 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
