<HEADLINE> Maldivian President Visits Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting President of the
Maldives Maumoon Abdul Gayoom and Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif will hold official talks Thursday on a wide range of issues
of mutual concern, officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gayoom, the outgoing chairman of the South Asian Association
for Regional Cooperation (SAARC), arrived here Wednesday evening
for a two-day official visit to Pakistan. He was greeted at the
airport by President Rafiq Tarar and Sharif who just flew back
from Qatar.
</P>
<P>
The Maldivian president is being accompanied by senior
government officials including the minister of state for
presidential affairs and deputy minister for foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, Gayoom and Sharif will discuss matters
relating to regional cooperation within the framework of SAARC as
well as the whole gamut of Pakistan-Maldives bilateral relations,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will discuss ways to consolidate and further
expand relations between Pakistan and the Maldives, they said.
</P>
