<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SAARC Urged to Launch Efforts for Regional Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Maldivian President Mamoon Abdul
Gayoom Wednesday expressed the hope that concerted efforts would
be launched from the forum of the South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC) to create harmony in the region.
</P>
<P>
Talking briefly to reporters on his arrival, Gayoom said the
main purpose of the seven-member regional grouping was to create
more understanding and harmony in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
He said that during his two-day visit he would discuss
bilateral issues and matters relating to SAARC with President
Rafiq Tarar and Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif.
</P>
<P>
He said matters pertaining to the forthcoming SAARC summit,
scheduled to take place in Colombo late this month, would also
come up for discussion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
