<HEADLINE> Dhaka Condemns Israeli Decision to Expand Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh on Wednesday condemned
Israel's decision to expand the boundaries of Jerusalem and
expressed its deep concern over the development.
</P>
<P>
An official statement said the Israeli decision on June 21 "is
a flagrant violation of international law and a breach of
bilateral accord, and it poses serious threat to peace, security
and stability in the region."
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi government hopes that good sense will prevail
and that the Israeli leadership will reverse the decision, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, at a U.N. Security Council meeting in New York on
Tuesday, Bangladesh Permanent Representative to the U.N.
Anwar-ul-Karim Chowdhury reaffirmed the country's support for the
establishment of a sovereign and independent Palestine with
Jerusalem as the capital, a press report said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the international community to reinject momentum
to the peace process and take all necessary measures and
initiatives to bring the peace process back on the track, the
report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
