<HEADLINE> Missile Explosion Destroying Farm Land in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- About 15 acres of farm and bush land
were destroyed Wednesday in a fire caused by an anti-aircraft
missile which exploded at Chordaki Akrotiri in the southern Greek
island of Crete.
</P>
<P>
During a training exercise, the "Nike" missile went off course
at an altitude of 4,000 feet. The Greek officer in charge of the
exercise then decided to press the self-destruct button and the
explosion was heard in the nearby town of Chania, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
It was believed that the burning fragments from the missile
caused the fire.  
</P>
</TEXT>
