<HEADLINE> New Seed Fund For UK Universities Opens For </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Seed funding for the UK universities
to help turn research into successful business is now available
through a new Government backed fund.
</P>
<P>
The University Challenge Fund aims to bridge the long existing
funding gap in the UK at the state when the results of research
are ready to be worked up into a potential commercial development,
the Department of Trade and Industry (DTI) announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Outline bids from universities are invited over the next four
months, with a deadline of October 20. Applicants meeting the
Fund's criteria will be selected to compete in the second stage,
running from December until early 1999.
</P>
<P>
Celebrating the launch of the Fund, in partnership with the
Wellcome Trust, Geoffrey Robinson, Paymaster General, said: "We
need a more vibrant entrepreneurial culture in our academic life
and a more scientifically streetwise business community if we are
to create powerful synergy between science and industry."
</P>
<P>
The Fund is regarded as a key step in helping to unleash
entrepreneurial spirit in the academic world and bringing science
and industry closer together. 
</P>
</TEXT>
