<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-01 16:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Clarifies Stand on Europe's Concerns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- In another attempt to dispel
Europe's concerns and worries towards Iran, Iranian President
Mohammad Khatami Wednesday clarified his country's policies,
saying they serve to remove tensions.
</P>
<P>
"We feel no enmity towards any party or country," Khatami said
in a meeting with visiting Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi,
the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
"At the same time, we expect others to respect our national
interests and the principles of friendship in their relations with
Iran," he added.
</P>
<P>
Khatami said that Iran attaches great importance to human
rights, adding that peace and human rights will be realized only
when all human beings enjoy suitable living rights.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the issue of weapons of mass destruction, Khatami
said that "Iran favors a region free from weapons of mass
destruction, including the nuclear weapons."
</P>
<P>
He called for a non-discriminatory approach to the issue of
nuclear non-proliferation.
</P>
<P>
Khatami was apparently responding to European Union's concerns
over Iran's alleged human rights abuses, attempts to undermine the
Middle East peace process and seek weapons of mass destruction,
and support for terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The EU has announced its readiness to hold dialog with Iran
over the concerns in a bid to establish a new bilateral
relationship.
</P>
<P>
The visit of the Italian prime minister, which started Tuesday,
is believed to help find ways to improve the EU-Iran relations
which were cooled down in Europe's various accusations against
Iran.
</P>
<P>
Khatami termed Italy as the cradle of the western civilization,
saying that a unique and friendly relation between Iran, which he
said is the cradle of the Islamic civilization. He called on Italy
to help realize the much promoted dialog amongst civilizations.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said that "we are of the belief that no problem in the
region can be solved without Iran's active participation."
</P>
<P>
"Peace and tranquillity in the Middle East can be brought
about only through participation of the important countries of
the region, including Iran," he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed confidence that dialog among civilizations will
bring about understanding among nations.
</P>
<P>
Noting that cultural exchanges can help Iran and Italy forge
closer ties in the international arena, Prodi said the formation
of Rome-Tehran joint commission next month will promote the
expansion of their cooperation in trade and industries.
</P>
<P>
Prodi received an honorary doctorate from Tehran University
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
