<HEADLINE> Beckham Likely to Serve Ban in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- England midfielder David Beckham will
serve a probable two-game ban in 2000 if he plays in the European
qualifying round for the 2002 World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
FIFA Director of Communications Keith Cooper said Wednesday that
Beckham would also be fined at least 5,000 Swiss Francs, the usual
disciplinary action for a red-carded player in the finals.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old was sent off in the 47th minute of Tuesday's
second-round game against Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Cooper said, "Any suspension is carried into the qualifying rounds
for the next World Cup, which will start in the autumn of the year
2000 following the European Championships."  
</P>
