<DOCNO> XIE19980702.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quarterfinal Against France Disappoints Chiesa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Enrico Chiesa was very
disappointed that his team have to play their World Cup quarterfinal
game against France.
</P>
<P>
The Parma forward said on Tuesday that "I'm very disappointed that
we have to play our next match against France. For me, it's the final
before the event."
</P>
<P>
He added, "Both teams know each other well and both are capable of
winning."
</P>
<P>
Chiesa said he also thinks Zinedine Zidane is one of the best
players in the world.
</P>
<P>
He added, "Playing France in the most beautiful stadium in the
country with enthusiastic fans will be great, even if they are
cheering against us."
</P>
<P>
Italy will play France in Stade de France in Saint-Denis outside
Paris on July 3. 
</P>
