but are expected to be known Thursday when the two envoys are
expected to give separate press conferences in Abuja and Lagos
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria has become focus of attention of the international
community since the sudden death of former military ruler General
Sani Abacha on June 8.
</P>
<P>
Western countries are determined to seize the change of leader
as an opportunity to bring Nigeria back to the world of
democracy, according to political watchers here. 
