<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inflation Stable in Euro Zone Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The inflation rate for the single
currency participating countries in the European Union (EU)
remained stable in May, the statistical office of the European
communities reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based Eurostat said the rate was 1.4 percent,
the same as one year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Also in May, the inflation rate for all 15 EU member states was
1.6 percent, in comparison with 1.5 percent one year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The highest rates were posted by Greece and Ireland with 5.0
percent and 2.4 percent respectively, while the lowest rates were
registered in France and Austria, both with 1.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
Across the EU, the inflation rate increased in six states
compared with April; decreased in another six and remained stable
in the remaining three.
</P>
<P>
The EU member states participating in the single currency
mechanism are Belgium, Germany, Spain, France, Ireland, Italy,
Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Austria, Portugal and Finland.
</P>
</TEXT>
