<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals Up in Nepal in First Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in Nepal
increased by 9.3 percent during the first six months of this year
compared with the same period of last year, the Department of
Tourism said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 181,209 tourists had visited Nepal through the air
route by the end of June as against 165,777 during the same period
last year, the department said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Visit Nepal Year '98 was launched in January with a target to
attract half a million tourists this year. Tourism is a major
foreign exchange earner for the Himalayan kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Tourist arrivals are generally low in Nepal during the months
of June and July, but the figures were encouraging this year due
to tourism promotion activities in India and some West European
countries, the department said.
</P>
<P>
It said the number of Indian tourists has risen by 19.8 percent
during the first six months, and is expected to go up further as
the Indian government has decided to provide duty-free baggage
facilities to the Indian tourists returning from Nepal by air.
</P>
<P>
However, the number of tourists from Singapore and Hong Kong
has declined by 20 and 25 percent respectively during the first
three months of this year, the department said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
