<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Goal-keeper Demands Recognition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Though due to set the all-time World Cup
appearence record for goal-keeper, Brazilian goalie Taffarel said he
still has not get the recognition he deserves.
</P>
<P>
Taffarel will play his 16th game in World Cup finals in the
quarter-final match between Brazil and Denmark on Friday, one more
than his compatriot Gilmar and Emerson Leao.
</P>
<P>
But Taffarel said he still tried hard to get the recognition he
deserved.
</P>
<P>
"In Brazil only strikers count. A goal-keeper is bad if he lets
in a goal, even if his team has won by six goals." Taffarel said.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Taffarel is a regular in the Brazilian team, but
he is not viewed as one of the stars as he is totally overshadowed
by Ronaldo, Rivaldo and Robert Carlos.
</P>
<P>
Taffarel said:"In Brazil people are crazy about football. But
they dream about wearing a number nine or number ten on their shirt.
If you're a goal-keeper you just don't exist." 
</P>
</TEXT>
