<HEADLINE> 19 Missing from Capsized Boat on Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- An iron barge capsized on the
Yangtze River near Yichang city in central China's Hubei Province
at around 4:30 this morning. Six people on board were rescued, but
19 were missing.
</P>
<P>
The boat, driven by a local farmer, turned upside down three
kilometers downstream of the Three Gorges Dam construction site.
</P>
<P>
A fire brigade rushed to the site to assist in the rescue
efforts.
</P>
<P>
Most of the passengers were farmers from Nantuo Village heading
for shopping in Bahekou Village.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is still under investigation.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze has been experiencing rising water flow in the pas
few days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
