<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bubka Hopes Brazil, France Play in Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's world pole vault record holder
Sergi Bubka said he was following the soccer World Cup competition
closely and hoped Brazil and host France would clash in the final.
</P>
<P>
"It would be great to see Brazil and France playing together in the
final," said the 33-year-old Bubka, who is an avid soccer fan.
</P>
<P>
"The level of play is excellent and the organization appears to be
very good as well, with every match booked out," said Bubka in Monaco.
</P>
<P>
Bubka, a fan of the defending champions Brazil, said his favorite
player was the team's star defender Roberto Carlos.
</P>
<P>
Proof of his love of the sport came earlier this year, with his
participation in April's "Star Team for Children" football match in
Monte Carlo.
</P>
<P>
He played alongside Price Albert of Monaco, motorcyling star Max
Biaggi, ski champion Alberto Tomba against a team of former Juventus
players.
</P>
<P>
"I played as a forward," said Bubka. "But I am equally at ease in
any position.. I just like to get out there and play."
</P>
<P>
