<HEADLINE> Enterprises Urged to Promote Innovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing today urged
enterprises across the country to improve their management systems
and promote technological innovation to keep their vigor and
competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, made the
call after he visited three high-tech enterprises -- the Stone
Group, Beijing San Huan New Materials High-Tech Company of the
Chinese Academy of Sciences and Zi Guang Group of Qinghua
University in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"We should support the development of hi-tech industries and
use the fruits of knowledge innovation to promote the overall
progress of the country's agriculture, industry and service
sector," he said. "This will help China maintain a sustainable
growth and become more competitive in the next century."
</P>
<P>
Li said the country will increase its investment and step up
the reform in colleges and research institutes, and support them
to cultivate more creative people for knowledge innovation.
</P>
<P>
The industrialization of scientific and technological results
is a key problem for knowledge innovation, he said, and
production, education and research should be combined more closely
to promote innovation.
</P>
<P>
He said officials at all levels should try to learn more about
the knowledge-based economy, abandon their traditional conceptions
and get ready for the challenges and opportunities brought by the
knowledge-based economy.
</P>
<P>
More young scientific personnel should be trained for
innovation work, while middle-aged and senior scientific workers
still play an active role, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the high-tech development zones all over the country
should be further improved to become the dynamic power behind
knowledge innovation, and more intermediary service organizations
should be established to promote the development of high-tech
industry.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the country will give stronger support to
knowledge innovation projects, which concern higher learning,
high-tech development and scientific studies.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will encourage the development of both state
and non-state high-tech enterprises, improve the legal protection
of intellectual property for both individuals and enterprises, and
try to attract more talented people for knowledge innovation from
both home and abroad. 
</P>
