<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Exchange Improves SSE 30 Index Selection Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange (SSE)
today issued new principles on the selection of 30 sample stocks
for the SSE 30 Index to make it more scientific, transparent and
fair.
</P>
<P>
Under the new policy, the exemplary issues will be chosen based
on the principle of "in line with the state policies on economic
development," instead of the previous "being able to represent the
region."
</P>
<P>
The change will make the index closer to the international
practice and in line with the general situation of the country's
economic development, according to an official at the bourse.
</P>
<P>
In the past, the SSE 30 Index samples were readjusted once
every three months, with no more than 10 percent of the stocks
replaced by others. From now on, check-ups on the sample will be
done once every six months to decide whether any one need to be
replaced.
</P>
<P>
A new expert consultative board will also be formed to replace
the former SSE Index Expert Committee, which will continue to be
responsible for the composition, selection and related work
concerning the SSE 30 Index.
</P>
<P>
The bourse began to publish the index in July of 1996, but only
one readjustment has been made on the samples. 
</P>
</TEXT>
