<HEADLINE> Discussions Underway in Somalia for Release of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, July 2 (Xinhua)-- Health situation of the two
French men kidnapped by Somali gunmen in the northeastern coast
of Alula Town is deteriorating, according to reports reaching here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
One of the two men is now seriously sick and unable to eat
while the other started fasting from all kinds of food in the
past three days.
</P>
<P>
The captors have moved their victims to Buro village, 45 km
East of the port town of Bossaso, where a delegation of elders
sent by the traditional and political leaders visited them this
week, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
According to one of the elders who had visited the French
hostages, the kidnappers have asserted that they won't accept
anything less than 75,000 US Dollars in exchange for the safe
release of the hostages.
</P>
<P>
The elders are currently having discussions with the United
Nations agencies in Bossaso over all possible ways for the
release of the hostages who remained in captivity since June 5.
</P>
<P>
The two French nationals and their small boat had been
kidnapped by somali gunmen off the coast of the Northeastern town
of Alula, about 200 km East of Bossaso early last month. The
victims said they are kidnapped when they were sailing as
tourists from the French port of Marseille through the Canal Suez
and that they were heading towards Madagascar. 
</P>
