Having been acknowledged by the CPP as its only candidate for
the premiership in the next government, Hun Sen believed the CPP
would win about 45 to 60 seats out of 122 seats in the National
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
However, he reaffirmed that if the CPP lost in the elections,
he would issue a statement and transfer power immediately and
peacefully.
</P>
<P>
Korishige Anami and his party arrived in Phnom Penh Wednesday
and was to return to home Thursday afternoon. The two sides
exchanged views on issues in the forthcoming elections.
</P>
<P>
Campaigning for the national elections officially began on June
25 and it will last one month.
</P>
<P>
Among the 39 political parties in the elections, the major
contenders are Hun Sen's CPP, Prince Ranariddh's royalist
Funcinpec and main opposition leader Sam Rainsy's Sam Rainsy
Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
