<HEADLINE> Chinese Insurance Company Donates Money to Flood-Hit Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The People's Insurance Company of
China (PICC) Property Insurance Co. Ltd. today donated 500,000
yuan to flood-ravaged areas in south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The money is intended to help resume production and rebuild
homes in the area.
</P>
<P>
Floods have raged in eastern, northern and central Guangxi
since mid-June, with nearly 80 percent of the region's 81 cities
and counties hit by floods. In many river-bound areas, both life
and property have been lost.
</P>
<P>
PICC Property is the first institution to donate money to
Guangxi's flooded areas.  
