<HEADLINE> b d p 1877 China-HK-LegCo HKSAR First LegCo Holds First Meeting with Rita Fan Elected President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The first meeting of the first
Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) ended here Thursday afternoon with Rita Fan elected its
president.
</P>
<P>
The 52-year-old Rita Fan, who was president of the former
Provisional Legislative Council, got 36 votes from the 60
legislators in a balloting while the other candidate Andrew Wong,
a university lecturer, lost in the race with 24 votes.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan delivered a short speech after the election, saying:
"I'm very honored to win support of a majority of legislators."
</P>
<P>
"I'll do my best to exercise my powers and functions in
accordance with Article 72 of the Basic Law without fear, favor
and selfishness," she said.
</P>
<P>
She pledged that in the next two years, the members of the
council will make every effort to serve the people of the SAR.
</P>
<P>
The meeting started at 3.30 p.m. with the 60 legislators taking
oath one by one.
</P>
<P>
During the oath-taking, all the legislators expressed their
determination to uphold the Basic Law, bear allegiance to the Hong
Kong SAR of the People's Republic of China and serve the Hong Kong
SAR in accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, legislator Leong Che-hung was elected to preside
over the election of the president of the LegCo. The election was
based on an election forum held by the Provisional Legislative
Council secretariat on June 29.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the legislators also approved Rules of
Procedure and a resolution on the timing of first meetings of the
House Committee, the Finance Committee and the Panels.
</P>
<P>
The first SAR Legislative Council which was produced by
election on May 24, consists of 60 members.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law, the term of office of the first SAR
Legislative Council is two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
