<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Book on Chinese Diplomacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 edition of "China's
Foreign Affairs" has been published by the World Knowledge
Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The new edition, which contains 750,000 Chinese characters,
highlights China's views on the international situation and lists
the nation's diplomatic activities during the previous year,
</P>
<P>
The edition, compiled by the Foreign Ministry's Policy Research
Office, describes the world situation in 1997 as "generally
exhibiting detente and stability", and notes that large countries
are engaged in unprecedented efforts to adjust relations in order
to form state-to-state relations geared to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The work notes that the relentless efforts to create a
"one-polar" world has been rebuffed by other nations amidst the
rapid and irresistible momentum towards global multipolarization.
</P>
<P>
It points out that the global economy continues to grow despite
the fact that steady growth in the future will be subject to
pressure resulting from the financial crisis sweeping many Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
The book describes China's diplomacy in 1997 as "fruitful." It
notes that China continues to observe its independent foreign
policy of peace and advocates new state-to-state relations
characterized by nonalignment, the elimination of confrontations
and not targeting third nations.
</P>
<P>
China strengthened friendly cooperative ties with countries
around the world during 1997, while at the same time tightening
good neighbor relations with surrounding nations through frequent
high-level contacts.
</P>
<P>
The book points out that China scored a breakthrough in Sino-US
relations and witnessed improving and developing relations with
other developed countries.
</P>
<P>
China has actively participated in multilateral international
and regional affairs and advocated a new concept of security.
</P>
<P>
China's resumption of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1,
1997, marked a major step in its peaceful reunification effort,
according to the edition.
</P>
<P>
It indicated that China firmly safeguardeds its sovereignty,
territorial integrity and national dignity, and has steadfastly
resisted all attempts to interfere in the nation's internal
affairs, as well as all other attempts to advocate "two Chinas" or
"one China, one Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
China also recorded new progress in foreign economic
activities. China's success in combating the Asian financial
crisis has readily exhibited the nation's contributions to global
financial and economic stability.
</P>
<P>
The edition includes an overview on global situation, with
articles on relations with other countries and international
organizations, wide-ranging agreements, regulations and laws of
governing the nation's diplomacy, as well as major diplomatic
speeches by Chinese leaders.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
