<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher on China Interest Rate Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks surged nearly 4
percent in post-holiday trading Thursday in the wake of the
interest rate cut in China.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index rose 323.06 points, or 3.78 percent, to
close at 8,866.16 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The local stock market was closed on Wednesday, a public
holiday marking Hong Kong's return to China on July 1 last year.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index gained 371.71 points, or 4.3 percent, to
register at 8,914.81 minutes after the opening of Thursday's
morning trade session.
</P>
<P>
The index rose 427.24 points, or 5.0 percent, to close at
8,970.34 at midday.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased by 3,512 million HK dollars (450
million U.S. dollars) to register at 7,982 million HK dollars
(1,023 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stock prices rose 82.39 points, or 0.97 percent, to
close at 8,543.10 on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
