<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Stocks Climb Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices continued to climb
in active dealings on Singapore Stock Market Thursday as the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) gained 29.77
points to close at 1,124.87 points, rising for the first time
above the level of 1,100 points for the past 10 days.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that blue chips rose on selective buying from the
start of the session.
</P>
<P>
But the initial euphoria over Japan plans to help its ailing
banking sector was weakened as the Japanese yen lost ground on
currency market, they said.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover increased to 215.63 million shares worth
354.21 million Singapore dollars (about 209.59 million U.S.
dollars). Gainers led losers by 169 to 110 with 310 stocks
remaining unchanged.
</P>
<P>
DBS Land was the most active stock with 16.75 million shares
traded. It was followed by Wing T which had 15.16 million units
done. Easykni thk was next with 15.07 million shares changing
hands.
</P>
<P>
The top gainer of the day was Creative 50 which gained 1.10
Singapore dollars to close at 22.10 Singapore dollars. SPH was up
70 cents to finish at 12.70 Singapore dollars. Asean rose by 50
cents to end at 5.80 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, CityDev was the biggest loser as it lost 17
cents to finish at 4.98 Singapore dollars. Liang HT was down 16
cents to end at 0.20 Singapore dollars. GE Life was next as it
shed 10 cents to close at 9.40 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
