<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigerian Gov't Cancels Ministries' Contracts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Head of State General
Abdulsalam Abubakar has ordered the cancellation of all contracts
awarded by federal ministries from June 8, the date of the sudden
death of former leader General Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
The cancellation was conveyed to all ministers and permanent
secretaries by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation,
Alhaji Gidado Idris, in a circular issued by the presidency on
June 26, the Guardian reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the circular, all contracts awarded before June
8, which did not receive either the approval of Abacha in writing
or that of the Federal Executive Council (the cabinet) were
similarly canceled.
</P>
<P>
The presidency said, henceforth, laid down procedure should be
followed in considering new contracts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
