<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Rate Reaches 3.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate between March
and May in Macao reached 3.8 percent, the highest in the past 18
months.
</P>
<P>
The Latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department on Thursday show that the jobless rate was 0.3 percent
higher than the same period last year, and 0.2 percent higher than
the February-April period this year.
</P>
<P>
The underemployment rate was recorded at 1.5 percent, the same
as the February-April period. But it was 0.6 percent higher than
the same March-May period last year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier figures released by the department show that there were
about 7,000 people out of job in the first quarter of 1998, when
the unemployment rate was 3.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Macao's economic slowdown started in 1993. The economic growth
rate for the past two years was both negative. 
</P>
</TEXT>
