<HEADLINE> Danish Referee Left Out of World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Danish referee Kim Nielsen has been
dropped by FIFA for the rest of the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Nielsen officiated at the match between England and Argentina
and got fierce criticism over his handling of the match in which he
sent off David Beckham and awarded two penalties.
</P>
<P>
Among the critics is football legend Pele who said the Danish
referee was obviously wrong in sending off Beckham.
</P>
<P>
FIFA has announced the list of referees who will continue to
officiate at the World Cup. Nielsen is not on the list of 10.
</P>
