<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Blames U.S. for Copyright Treaty Delay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam blamed the United States on
Thursday for the delay in ratifying a copyright treaty between
the two countries, the Vietnamese News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam ratified the treaty on December 26, 1997 before the
deadline set by the two countries when the document was signed on
June 27, 1997, said Vu Manh Chu, an official with the Ministry of
Culture and Information.
</P>
<P>
But the U.S. side has yet to ratify the document, said Chu.
</P>
<P>
Chu said that his country has made preparations for the
implementation of the treaty by organizing workshops on the treaty
for the relevant agencies and organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
