<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Garrison Protect HKSAR Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Visitors to the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) naval base on the Stonecutter Island, the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), can enjoy
watching flocks of sea birds which inhabit the area.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 kites transit Stonecutter Island every summer and
winter. The sound ecological environment on the island has been
attributed to extensive protection efforts undertaken by PLA
officers and soldiers in the year since China's resumption of
sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The PLA garrison consider the protection of natural resources
and environmental conditions on military bases as one of their
most important tasks, according to PLA officials.
</P>
<P>
A senior officer noted that special attention has been paid to
protecting over 100 species of birds and various wild animals
living in the area.
</P>
<P>
The garrison have planted numerous trees and a variety of
plants and flowers on bases to improve the natural habitats for
birds and animals.
</P>
<P>
Members of the PLA have also conducted regular land and sea
projects to remove garbage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
