<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Volkswagen Produces One Million Santanas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Volkswagen Automotive
Company Ltd. had manufactured slightly over a million Santana cars
by Wednesday to become China's leading automobile manufacturer.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-German venture reached the milestone after 13 years of
operation. Santana model vehicles are currently produced with 92
percent of related parts and components produced domestically,
compared to a mere 2.7 percent when the venture commenced
operations in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Volkswagen has an annual production capacity of
300,000 Santanas, with parts provided by over 300 suppliers and
after-sale services by 400 maintenance centers. Santas have
approximately a half of China's car market.
</P>
<P>
The venture produced some 230,000 vehicles in 1997, 26.3
billion yuan in sales for the year, ranking first amongst China's
top 500 foreign-funded industrial enterprises for the sixth
consecutive year. Shanghai Volkswagen also spent 800 million yuan
establishing a technical center to promote greater development.
</P>
<P>
The company's record period output for the first half of this
year exceeded 120,000 units, or 664 cars daily. The new Santana
2000-GSI has achieved positive results since being introduced to
the market in March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
