<HEADLINE> ADB to Grant For Sri Lanka's Tea Small Holding Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
has agreed to grant 30 million U.S. dollars to develop Sri Lanka's
tea small holding sector, according to the ADB sources here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This is to continue the second phase of the on-going
development project started earlier this year when the ADB granted
9.3 million dollars for the first phase of this project.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the project will replant 500 hectares and
refill 800 hectares per year in a six-year period.
</P>
<P>
Tea small holders will be given a subsidy of 40 percent of the
total cost of replanting in the country.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the project will boost the production of
quality tea and increase the volume of production in this sector.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Tea Small Holdings Authority has been
encouraging replanting as extensively as possible and has been
providing seedlings and high breed clones. 
</P>
