<HEADLINE> Seven Northeastern Cities Join Hands to Expand Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Seven cities in northeast China's
Liaoning Province have formed a joint organization to share local
resources to develop tourism.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang, Dalian, Anshan, Fushun, Benxi, Yingkou and
Dandong recently signed an agreement to join the broad-based
tourism framework.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for the cities to establish inter-service
networks covering tourism information, products and transportation.
</P>
<P>
The cities will organize bus tours, market related tickets on
behalf of other network members, introduce accommodations and
jointly publish tourism leaflets, video programs and photo albums.
</P>
<P>
Local officials note that move will promote both the rational
use of tourism resources in member cities and the rapid growth of
tourism in the region as a whole. 
</P>
