<HEADLINE> Stone Tablet Forest In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province has
plans for a stone forest to protect the stone tablets that have
been carved there over the past two thousand or more years.
</P>
<P>
The province was the home of Confucius, the philosopher and
educator of the Spring and Autumn Period (770-476 B.C.) and has
many stone tablets with inscriptions written by prominent people
in subsequent dynasties.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the stone tablet forest will be built in
Changqing County on 67 hectares of land. They say that they are
now busy collecting stone tablets from around the province and
other parts of China. 
