confidence of the Hong Kong people in overcoming the temporary
economic difficulties caused by the Asian financial turmoil,
local newspapers commented here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"President Jiang Zemin gave very positive comments on the
successful implementation in Hong Kong of the concept of 'one
country, two systems' and the achievements scored by the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) government led by Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa. He also reaffirmed the central
government's strong support to the SAR government," said the
Chinese-language newspaper Wen Wei Po in an editorial Thursday.
</P>
