six-point "active supports" to the HKSAR government concerning
Hong Kong's finance and economy, tourism, investment in the inland
areas, high technologies and infrastructure, re-exports vis Hong
Kong and international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"They will serve as a big encouragement to Hong Kong's economic
development," the paper stressed.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong is in a more favorable position than others and has
more room for maneuver in combating the temporary economic
difficulties as it enjoys the backing of the motherland with a
population of 1.2 billion and a fast-growing and prosperous
economy," the newspaper added.
</P>
<P>
The six-point "active supports" offered by President Jiang
greatly encouraged the Hong Kong people, and the latest decrease
of interbank rates beginning July 1 in the inland areas also
served as a support to Hong Kong's economy, said Hong Kong
Commercial Daily said Thursday in an editorial.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang spoke highly of the Hong Kong people who carry
on the tradition of loving the motherland and loving Hong Kong and
keep working as masters of the land, contributing to the
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong, Ta Kung Pao noted.
</P>
<P>
"This sense of responsibility and the spirit of working as
masters of the country are an important factor for building an
even better Hong Kong," the newspaper said. 
