<HEADLINE> Southernmost Hainan Province Wooking to Achieve 8 Percent Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- China's southernmost Hainan province
will take effective measures to ensure eight percent growth rate
in the economy this year.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period, local agriculture and service
sectors grew rapidly, while investment in fixed assets and local
revenues were up by a big margin from the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural added value output is expected to rise by 8
percent this year, with per-capita income of farmers expected to
reach 2,500 yuan (300 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
To reach its goal, the province will attatch importance to fine
crop strains and wide-spread use of practical agricultural
technology, by promoting the use of 100 technologies this year,
and speeding up construction of wholesale farm and sideline
products markets and information outlets for vegetable and fruit
distribution.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, it will try to develop ocean fishing by giving
priority to the offshore aquaculture and will reform local state
businesses and help them to increase economic returns. And Hainan
will also ensure a moderate increase in fixed assets spendings.
</P>
