<HEADLINE> Increasing Fixed Asset Investment In Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
allocated 16.4 billion yuan for fixed assets investment in the
first five months of this year, as part of the move to increase
local demand.
</P>
<P>
This represents a 41 percent increase in the investment from
the same period of last year, a level that is 28 percent higher
than the national average, according to the Provincial Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
In the five-month period, the provincial government approved
546 new projects, 264 more than for the same period last
year. Major projects included the Mianhuatan Hydroelectric Power
Station and the Meizhou Thermal Power Station.
</P>
<P>
Residential housing sales were up an amazing 97.8 percent in
the first five months, at 778,000 sq.m. of floor space.
</P>
<P>
Local economists attribute the increase in government
investment to a concerted effort in many parts of Fujian, and to
more simplified formalities and closer coordination between the
government and key project supervisors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
