<HEADLINE> Bus Overturns in Turkey, Killing 15 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 passengers were killed
and 22 others injured Wednesday night when a bus overturned and
caught fire in southeastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the bus, from southern city of Adana to
southeastern city of Diyarbakir, hit a cow at about 50 kilometers
from Diyarbakir and turned over to a shoulder of the
Siverek-Diyarbakir highway.
</P>
<P>
The overturned bus burnt into flames immediately and 15
passengers were trapped inside and burnt to death.
</P>
<P>
The fire has been put out and the injured have been taken to
hospital for treatment, added the agency. 
</P>
