<BODY>
<HEADLINE> President Jiang Inspects PLA Troops in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
Thursday morning inspected the People's Liberation Army (PLA)
troops stationed in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) at the Stonecutters Island Naval Base.
</P>
<P>
When Jiang arrived at the naval base, he was greeted by General
Tao Bojun, commander of the Guangzhou Military Area Command of the
PLA, and leaders of the HKSAR Garrison.
</P>
<P>
In the company of PLA Chief of General Staff General Fu Quanyou
and HKSAR Garrison Commander Lieutenant General Liu Zhenwu, Jiang,
who is also general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, reviewed the guard of honor of the three
services of the PLA garrison troops stationed in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
After the inspection, Jiang addressed a gathering of officers,
praising the garrison troops for having done well in the past year
since Hong Kong returned to China on July 1, 1997 with support and
help from the SAR government headed by Mr. Tung Chee Hwa.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that he was pleased to visit the PLA troops
stationed in Hong Kong on the occasion of the first anniversary of
Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang came to Hong Kong from Beijing Tuesday afternoon to
attend celebrations of the first anniversary of Hong Kong's
return to China and of the establishment of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Jiang extended his best regards to the officers and men of the
garrison on behalf of the CPC Central Committee, the State Council
and the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China's resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong is a major gratifying event to all the
Chinese people including Hong Kong compatriots and overseas
Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The president said that in the past year the SAR government
headed by Mr. Tung Chee Hwa has achieved great successes under the
guidance of the correct policies and principles of the central
authorities.
</P>
<P>
He told the officers that he believed Hong Kong, under the
leadership of the SAR government, will overcome the temporary
difficulties caused by the Asian financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that during his stay in Hong Kong he has felt the
enthusiasm and unity of the Hong Kong people. This enthusiasm and
unity, together with other factors such as a sound economic legal
system, a solid economic foundation and a great number of well
educated and trained mangement personnel in the local business and
financial sectors, Hong Kong can certainly ride out of the
difficulties, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, as the supreme commander of the PLA, called on the
officers and men of the garrison in Hong Kong to continue to
strictly abide by the Basic Law, the Garrison Law and laws of the
HKSAR and to do their work better.
</P>
<P>
Among those present on the occasion were Qian Qichen,
vice-premier of the State Council; Zeng Qinghong, alternate member
of the Political Bureau, member of the secretariat, and director
of the General Office, of the CPC Central Committee; and Tung
Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong SAR Government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
