<HEADLINE> Philippines' Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' aggregate receipts
from merchandise exports grew by 20.3 percent to 11.5 billion U.S.
dollars for the first five months this year from 9.6 billion
dollars a year earlier, the National Statistics Office said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
For May alone, the country's exports receipts increased by 21.8
percent to 2.4 billion dollars from 1.98 billion dollars for the
same month last year, according to figures released by the office.
</P>
<P>
Electronics and Components remained the country's top dollar
earner with its exports growing by 2.17 percent to 1.1 billion
dollars in May.
</P>
<P>
The other major dollar earners were articles of apparel and
clothing and coconut oil.
</P>
<P>
The United States remained the largest overseas market for the
Philippines' products, with its imports totaling 3.8 billion
dollars during the first five months of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
