<HEADLINE> Israeli Shelling Kills Lebanese Civilian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A Lebanese civilian was killed in
Israeli troops' shelling on villages in south Lebanon early
Thursday morning, the Voice of the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese civilian was killed when Israeli shells landed at
the village of Hadaita on the edge of the western sector of the
Israeli occupied area in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israeli troops also heavily bombarded other villages along the
occupied zone with the assistance of helicopters, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli attacks came immediately after the Hadaita post,
which has long been held by Israeli troops, was seized by the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah said in a statement that from 5:20 am local time (GMT
0200), its fighters began to launch offensives against Israeli
posts along the northern edge of the occupied zone and eventually
took control of the post at Hadaita.
</P>
<P>
Israeli army sources said three of its soldiers and one member
of its allied South Lebanese Army (SLA) were wounded in clashes
with Lebanese guerrillas. One of them is in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Israel occupied a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim to protect its northern
border from cross-border guerrilla attacks.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah is the most active Muslim group in Lebanon to fight
against the 2,000-strong Israeli occupying forces and the 2,500
SLA militiamen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
