<HEADLINE> Beijing University Set to Offer Women's Studies Course </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University (Beida), one of
China's most prestigious universities, will offer a course of new
postgraduate Women's Studies beginning in September.
</P>
<P>
The course will be offered with the approval of the State
Council's Academic Degrees Committee.
</P>
<P>
Beida will become the first Chinese university to offer a
postgraduate course dedicated to studies involving women. However,
Women's Studies were introduced on the undergraduate level during
the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Beida will focus on theoretical studies of the women's affairs
since the Fourth World Conference on Women held in Beijing in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Beida Research Center on Chinese and Foreign Women will
administer the new teaching program.
</P>
<P>
The center was set up in 1990 and has since recorded major
achievements in studies related the relationship of women to
culture, history, law, society, education, psychology, population
and the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
