<DOCNO> XIE19980702.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China University Receives Certificate Of Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Dalian Maritime University in
China's northeast Liaoning Province has been given certificates of
authentication by the Norway Classification Society.
</P>
<P>
Four quality standards -- the ISO9001 quality system, the
Norway Classification Society, the maritime training center
management standards, and nautical simulated articles center
management standards -- mean that Dalian Maritime is the first
university in the world to meet the requirements of Standards of
Training, Certification and Watchkeeping for Seafarers 1978, as
amended in 1995.
</P>
<P>
As the amount of ocean shipping increases, shipping industry
need for educated and trained seafarers are becoming more
acute. Studies have found that more than 80 percent of the
maritime accidents were caused by human factors.
</P>
<P>
The International Maritime Organization noted that nautical
education and training organizations should have systems of
standardization that guarantee the quality of training and the
standards, which will be fully implemented on Feburary 1, 2002,
mean that signatory nations will not acknowledge certificates of
seafarers' sea worthiness issued by a country which violates those
standards.
</P>
<P>
China is one of the signatory nations of the STCW
Covenant. Dalian Maritime University, the biggest university of
nautical education in China, was listed as one of the most famous
maritime universities in the world by the International Maritime
Organization (IMO) in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The university began to establish a quality security system
that met international standards last year. The quality security
system was given certificates of authentication by the Norway
Classification Society and the China Maritime Supervisory Bureau
this June.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
