China helped Zimbabwe train a lot of freedom fighters, making the
major contributions to the country's independence.
</P>
<P>
Since independence in 1980, Zimbabwe continued to get China's
assistance in training its senior officers and technicians, he
said, adding the Zimbabwean army and people would never forget
the disinterested assistance China rendered to his country.
</P>
<P>
The general also told the Chinese delegation that the
Zimbabwean armed forces are now embarking on streamlining reform
and modern training. He hoped China would continue to assist in
its military training.
</P>
<P>
Major General Sun Qixiang, head of the Chinese delegation and
deputy director of the foreign affairs office of the Chinese
Defense Ministry, reviewed the history of friendly cooperation
between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that China would, as always, support the Zimbabwean
army's construction.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed gratitude to the Zimbabwean government for
its support to China on issues regarding Taiwan and human right.
