<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980702.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Painful Reform in Thailand: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
However, the side effects of the IMF remedies are also evident.
Critics insist that the economic situation has got worse since the
IMF-initiated reforms were launched. For one thing, exports have
not shown any signs of a pickup, registering a negative growth of
2.7 percent in the first four months of this year. It is obvious
that currency devaluation is not helping Thai exports because all
neighboring countries, which are Thailand's competitors, have also
been suffering from competitive devaluations.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the extraordinarily high interest rates and the huge
amount of non-performing loans in the financial system have
combined to plunge the Thai economy into a recession, raising
fears as to whether the recession will develop into a full-blown
depression.
</P>
<P>
The liquidity crunch, a by-product of the tight monetary
policy, has become a drag on economic recovery. Experts say
Thailand needs 26.1 billion dollars in capital inflow over the
next 12 months to overcome the present tight liquidity.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the drastic reform, a total of 3,961 enterprises
were closed down between January and May this year, boosting the
number of the unemployed to 2.7 million.
</P>
<P>
Economic hardships have degraded living standards by more than
20 percent, driving more and more people to below the poverty
line.
</P>
<P>
Despite these adverse consequences, the Thai government has
pledged to continue the reform. Government officials have
indicated that Thailand has no choice but to stick to the IMF
remedies and the Thai people have to wait for the IMF medicine to
work.
</P>
<P>
Economic experts predicted that it might take three more years
for the Thai economy to show any sustainable signs of growth. At
present, only one thing is clear: The next three to four months
will be most critical for the country as the economy is expected
to hit rock bottom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980702.0243 </DOCNO>
