<DOCNO> XIE19980702.0260 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> President Jiang Opens Hong Kong New Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
Thursday opened the new Hong Kong International Airport, a
multi-billion-dollar project that took eight years to build for
the aviation growth into the next century.
</P>
<P>
At a grand opening ceremony Thursday morning, Jiang unveiled a
commemorative plaque before a crowd of more than 3,000 guests
clustering in the passenger terminal, a Y-shaped building claimed
to be the world's most spacious airport terminal.
</P>
<P>
The new airport is constructed on a 1,248-hectare reclaimed
site at Chek Lap Kok off the northern coast of Lantau Island, 25
kilometers west of the Hong Kong Island. Operating around the
clock, the airport has a designed capacity of handling 35 million
passengers and three million tons of cargo a year.
</P>
<P>
"The new international airport is one of the most advanced
airports in today's world," said Vice-Premier Qian Qichen at the
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that the opening of the new airport would not only
give a tremendous impetus to the exchanges between Hong Kong and
the mainland, and between Hong Kong and other parts of the world,
but would also help consolidate Hong Kong's status as an
international or regional center of finance, trade, aviation and
tourism, enhance its competitiveness, and inject new vitality to
the economic development of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), said on the same occasion: "The grand
opening of the new Hong Kong International Airport is a
combination of the wisdom, diligence and entrepreneurship of the
Hong Kong people and symbolizes the brilliant prospects of Hong
Kong."
</P>
<P>
The new airport is part of the ten infrastructure projects
collectively known as the Airport Core Program, one of the biggest
civil engineering undertakings in the world, built at a cost of
155 billion HK dollars (20 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
"The new airport is an amazing engineering project, in which
everyone in Hong Kong takes pride," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Following the completion of the new airport, the SAR government
will invest 235 billion HK dollars (30 billion U.S. dollars) in
the five years to come on a package of large-scale infrastructure
projects, according to the Chief Executive.
</P>
<P>
He stressed: "These massive projects bear further testimony to
the ability and determination of the people of Hong Kong. They
once again prove that Hong Kong will always be a city of vigor and
opportunity."
</P>
<P>
Wong Po-yan, Chairman of the Airport Authority (AA), spoke
highly of the hard work in the construction of the new airport by
local communities, companies from the mainland and over 25 foreign
countries. The AA is a statutory body primarily responsible for
the designing, construction and management of the new airport.
</P>
<P>
A variety of cultural and entertainment programs were staged at
the three-hour-long opening gala, including a dancing dragon
formed by 500 people, a lion dance, a children's choir,
instrumental music, and a video show.
</P>
<P>
Among the guests at the opening ceremony were senior central
government officials, principal officials of the SAR, foreign
government representatives, chairmen of other airport authorities,
and those involved in the new airport construction and operation.
</P>
<P>
The new airport will be opened for commercial aviation on July
6 after a dramatic overnight move of airport operations from Kai
Tak to Chek Lap Kok. 
</P>
</TEXT>
