<HEADLINE> Panamanian Legislature to Discuss Amendment of Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Panamanian legislative
assembly will hold a series of extraordinary sessions this month
to discuss the Panamanian Defense Regulation, the amendment of a
law on retirement and other issues.
</P>
<P>
In remarks released by the local media Wednesday, Legislator
Cesar Sanjur said that on top of the agenda of the meetings will
be the amendment of a 1954 law stipulating that any government
officers older than 75 years should retire and get a pension.
</P>
<P>
The extraordinaries sessions will take place on July 6-17,
according to local media reports.
</P>
<P>
The Legislative Assembly will also discuss a bill about
official translators and a separate bill on the obligation to sing
the Panamanian National Anthem.
</P>
<P>
During a series of earlier sessions which ended on Wednesday,
the Legislative Assembly approved 38 bills including a bill on
presidential reelection.
</P>
<P>
The legislators also aproved a reform bill that allows the
making of arbitration decisions by the Labor Board in handling
labor disputes, a law on environment protection and a law on
legislative service. 
</P>
