<HEADLINE> Yunnan Enforcing Ban On Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- An Autonomous Prefecture of Dai
and Jingpo ethnic minorities in southwest China's Yunnan Province
has been cracking down on drug-related crimes.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, police there dealt with 1,883 drug-smuggling cases,
arresting 2,267 people, and confiscated 1,267 kilograms of heroin,
185 kilograms of opium, and a kilogram of "ice".
</P>
<P>
The prefecture shares a 503 kilometer border with Myanmar
national and has a hard time dealing with drug-related crimes.
</P>
<P>
It has also helped 9,788 addicts kick the drug habit. 
</P>
