<HEADLINE> Italian FM Warns Ethnic Albanians of War Risk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Italian Foreign Minister
Lamberto Dini said here Wednesday that the persistence with the
idea of independence for Kosovo could spark a new war across the
whole region.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference with his Romanian counterpart
Andrei Plesu, Dini said larger autonomy for the Serbian province
of Kosovo was the only way to solve the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslavian authorities had already hinted that they would
accept the proposal, but the international community should put
further pressure on Kosovo's ethnic Albanians and the Albanian
authorities to make them understand that persisting with the idea
of independence could trigger a war, said Dini.
</P>
<P>
Plesu said it was possible to solve the Kosovo crisis through
political means, adding that the Balkan countries should
strengthen cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers agreed that it was imperative for their
two countries to further cooperation in all fields and renew joint
projects within the framework of the strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
Dini also said Italy would continue to back Romania's accession
to the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
The Italian foreign minister said he was optimistic that
Romania and Slovakia would join NATO in the bloc's second wave of
expansion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
