<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province Promotes Ethnic Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Qinghai Province
has raised more than 500 million yuan to develop local ethnic
education.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used to rebuild school buildings and provide
education for more than 90 percent of the ethnic school-age
children.
</P>
<P>
There are a number of ethnic groups in Qinghai, accounting for
42 percent of the provincial population.
</P>
<P>
The 99.6 million yuan from the World Bank will be used to set
up school facilities, buy teaching instruments and host training
programs for teachers in 14 poverty-stricken counties.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the province will use nearly 50 million yuan
from the central government and education department to build
dozens of primary and middle schools in ethnic areas.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province has received more than 300 million
yuan in educational funds from several national educational
projects such as Hope Project, Spring Bud Project, and State
Compulsory Education Project in Poverty-Stricken Regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
