<HEADLINE> Davenport, Seles Crash out of Wimbledon Quarter-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Lindsay Davenport of the
United States fell down at the quarter-final hurdle of the 1998
Wimbledon Tennis Championships after losing in straight sets 6-3,
6-3 to French player Nathalie Tzuziat.
</P>
<P>
Another major American upset at the two-week tournament is
sixth seed Monica Seles, who also lost in straight sets 7-6, 6-2
to little known player Natasha Zvereva of Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, defending champion Martina Hingis of Switzerland and
third seed Jana Novotna of the Czech republic swept aside their
seeded opponents Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain and American
player Venus Williams, cruising into a head-to-head semi-final
confrontation to be held Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the men's quarter-final clashes, 12th-seeded Briton Tim
Henman, who was encouraged by brilliant home supporters, outplayed
third seed Petra Korda of Czech Republic in straight sets 6-3,
6-4, 6-2 and became the first British Wimbledon semi-finalist in
25 years.
</P>
<P>
The other major star players including defending champion
American Pete Sampras, Croatian veteran Goran Ivanisevic and 1996
Wimbledon champion Richard Krajisec of the Netherlands all booked
their places in the semi-finals to be played on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
