<HEADLINE> Moscow Unveils World Youth Games Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Moscow held a grand ceremony
Wednesday unveiling the Olympic village for the first World Youth
Games in the center of the Russian capital.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Yuri Luzhkov and Russian Olympic Committee President
Vitaly Smirnov attended the ceremony in the Olympic compound,
which was built in 18 months for the games scheduled for July
11-19.
</P>
<P>
Luzhkov said the village will be able to comfortably house over
10,000 athletes from 137 countries and regions contesting in 15
sports.
</P>
<P>
The 15 categories will be athletics, basketball, fencing,
football, free-style wrestling, Greco-Roman wrestling, gymnastics,
handball, judo, rhythmic gymnastics, synchronous swimming,
swimming, table tennis, tennis, and volleyball.
</P>
<P>
The mayor called on the world community to cease all
hostilities during the games and contribute to peace and
stability on Earth.
</P>
<P>
The village's first inhabitants would be the Brazilian team,
who will arrive on July 3. 
</P>
