<HEADLINE> Illicit Drugs to Be Destroyed in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATION, July 1 (Xinhua) -- About 50 tons of illicit
drugs, including opium, heroin and morphine, will be destroyed in
Tehran, Iran, Thursday, U.N. spokesman Juan Carlos Brandt
announced here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The street value of the drugs is estimated at 700 million U.S.
dollars, Carlos said.
</P>
<P>
The event should be seen as a measure of dedication and
commitment of the Iranian government concerning the fight against
illicit drugs in view of the large amount of the drugs to be
destroyed, he told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami and his guest, Executive
Director of the United Nations International Drug Control Program
Pino Alarcchi, will be present at the ceremony due to take place
at 5:00 p.m. local time, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
