<HEADLINE> Iowa Republicans Schedule 1999 Presidential Straw Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The state's Republican Party of
Iowa in the United States has already scheduled a high-profile
straw poll of presidential candidates in the summer of 1999.
</P>
<P>
"Even though the race hasn't started yet, we thought we should
set the date of the first real presidential hurdle," Keith
Fortmann, executive director of the Iowa Republican Party, was
quoted by the Associated Press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Fortmann said Republican officials will conduct an Iowa Straw
Poll on August 14, 1999, at Iowa State University in Ames. During
past campaigns, similar events have drawn thousands of people as
presidential candidates competed with each other.
</P>
<P>
Iowa's precinct caucuses will mark the opening of the
presidential nominating season in 2000, and candidates are already
spending considerable time in the state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
