<HEADLINE> Eight Dead in Accidents in Arizona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed in
Arizona Wednesday morning when a semi-tractor trailer ran over
and crushed a car that followed another fatal traffic accident,
the Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The accidents occurred on Interstate 10 about 65 kilometers
west of Phoenix. In the first accident, a man changing a tire was
struck and killed by a vehicle that drifted into the emergency
lane.
</P>
<P>
The second accident followed about a kilometer west of the
first. A semi van ran into the back of another semi that had
slowed as traffic choked up because of the first accident.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the rear truck was killed, and the front truck
rolled over and nearly flattened a sedan ahead of it. Two adults
and four children were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
